# Standing Yoke Template -- Canonical Bishop -> Knight Dispatch Pattern

**Source:** Bishop maintains. Last updated 2026-06-10 by SEG-YOKE-TEMPLATE-EMBED.
**Purpose:** Every Bishop SEG authoring a new Knight Yoke uses this template as starting point. Embeds the §3 binding so each Yoke independently carries the discipline.

---

## Template Structure (copy + customize)

```markdown
<!-- bishop-yoke-task <ISO-8601-UTC> -->

## <EMOJI> BISHOP -> KNIGHT - TASK - <SCOPE-TITLE> - USE SONNET 4.6 SEGs (Statute §3)

**Pinned-class task. Pin-marker: <BP_NNN>_<SCOPE>_<UTC>**

> **🔐 STATUTE §3 + CORRECTIVE BP079 BINDING:** Every dispatch announcement uses the verbatim phrase "Sonnet 4.6". Never "Sonnet 4.5" or version-variant. Parent: `canon_statute_3_sonnet_4_6_sub_agent_default_every_dispatch_explicit_model_param_bp077` (pearl_8b0c6fb05fd9f38a). Corrective: `canon_statute_3_corrective_announcement_language_must_say_sonnet_4_6_verbatim_pattern_violation_bp079` (pearl_98f74effb5d986a5). Pre-dispatch self-audit: parameter AND announcement compliance both required.

### TL;DR
<1-2 sentence summary of what Knight is being asked to do>

### Why this matters
<Truth-Always: brief context of how this fits into current BP arc>

### What Knight needs to do
<SEG fan-out specification, Sonnet 4.6 SEGs mandatory, each SEG scoped>

### Reply contract
<What Knight returns: paths, byte counts, commits, screenshots, etc.>

### Statute reminders
- §3 (this Yoke binds both surfaces -- parameter + announcement)
- §12 Ask-Knight-First (if operational truth involved)
- canon_actual_runtime_verify_for_runtime_bugs_bp078 (for runtime bugs)
- canon_long_running_progress_heartbeat_canon_bp078 (for >3s operations)
- feedback_ux_seg_screenshot_mandatory_bp078 (for UX-touching surfaces)

### Paste-ready Founder wake-up
> Knight, NEW Yoke at `<canonical-path>`. <one-line scope>. Sonnet 4.6 SEGs mandatory (Statute §3 + corrective sub-canon BP079). Yoke-return consolidated.

- Bishop - BP<NNN> - pinned <ISO-8601-UTC>
```

---

## MANDATORY: Black Mamba Paste-Ready Dispatch Block

**Every Knight Yoke ships with a copy-paste-bomb at the bottom that Founder forwards to Knight verbatim. Self-contained. Knight executes from the paste alone -- no need to read the Yoke file first.**

Founder critique 2026-06-10 made this binding: "ALWAYS have a Black Mamba x some number, 10, 12, whatever it takes, instead of me wasting tokens on Knight figuring it out for himself." Decomposition is Bishop's job. Knight executes.

### Required block structure

```markdown
---

## BLACK MAMBA PASTE-READY DISPATCH (forward this block verbatim to Knight)

Knight: dispatch <N> parallel Sonnet 4.6 SEGs RIGHT NOW. Sonnet 4.6 verbatim in every announcement (Statute §3 + corrective sub-canon BP079, pearl_98f74effb5d986a5). Each SEG below is self-contained scope; do NOT re-decompose; do NOT ask for clarification before firing; fire all N in parallel single message.

**SEG-<id>-1 (Sonnet 4.6):** <self-contained scope -- file paths, commands, expected output>
**SEG-<id>-2 (Sonnet 4.6):** <self-contained scope>
**SEG-<id>-3 (Sonnet 4.6):** <self-contained scope>
...
**SEG-<id>-N (Sonnet 4.6):** <self-contained scope>

When all N SEGs return, run sequential synthesis: **SEG-<id>-VERIFY** (E2E test, screenshot per `feedback_ux_seg_screenshot_mandatory_bp078` if UX-touching) then **SEG-<id>-SHIP** (commit + push + tag + Cephas deploy + Yoke-return).

Yoke-return: append `## RESPONSE` block to this Yoke file at canonical path, including per-SEG commit SHA + key outcome + Truth-Always findings + any open obligations.

If any SEG announces "Sonnet 4.5" or other version-variant in narration: STOP, fix the announcement, re-fire. Violation of corrective sub-canon BP079.

---
```

### Authoring discipline (binding for any Bishop SEG authoring a new Yoke)

1. **Decompose BEFORE writing the Yoke.** Bishop sits with the spec, identifies N independent workstreams, names each SEG by canonical short ID (SEG-MC-1, SEG-RC-A-1, etc.), drafts scope per SEG. Knight does NOT redo this.
2. **Each SEG scope is self-contained.** File paths, table names, function names, expected output -- all in the SEG bullet. Knight reads ONE bullet, fires ONE SEG, gets the answer. No "see Bishop's spec doc §X" -- paste the relevant fragment.
3. **N is whatever it takes.** 3 SEGs for small work. 9-12 SEGs for medium. Up to 20+ for large parallel sweeps (e.g., a Drekaskip-class survey). Founder said "10, 12, whatever it takes" -- don't artificially cap.
4. **Pre-batch synthesis steps.** SEG-VERIFY and SEG-SHIP are always sequential after parallel batch. Specify them in the same paste-bomb.
5. **Block goes at BOTTOM of the Yoke** (so Founder scrolls to the end and finds the dispatch ready to copy).
6. **Block is preceded by `---` separator** so the copy boundary is obvious.
7. **No external references that require Knight to open files.** If the spec doc has critical config (paths, ports, table names), inline it in the paste-bomb. The Yoke file is the deep spec; the Black Mamba block is the dispatch.

### Why this works without MCP

Until Mnemosyne Come ships (Wave D), the cohort lacks shared substrate context. The Black Mamba paste-bomb is the substrate substitute: it carries the full context Knight needs. Founder paste-bombs once, Knight executes literally. No re-decomposition. No "Knight figures it out."

Composes with `canon_designed_to_be_copied_autonomous_propagation_doctrine_bp051` at the dispatch layer -- the paste-bomb is the canonical orchestration artifact, copyable + self-contained.

---

## Discipline (binding for any Bishop SEG authoring a new Yoke)

1. **Always include the STATUTE §3 + CORRECTIVE BP079 BINDING block** verbatim. Copy-paste it. Don't paraphrase.
2. **Always use "Sonnet 4.6" verbatim** in the Yoke title line + SEG fan-out + reply contract + paste-ready wake-up. Never "Sonnet 4.5" or version-variant.
3. **Always deposit at canonical path** `BISHOP_DROPZONE\01_KnightPrompts\PROMPT_KNIGHT_BP<NNN>_<SCOPE>_<DATE>.md`.
4. **Always update KNIGHT_QUEUE.md** with new active entry at appropriate priority.
5. **Always include paste-ready Founder wake-up** at the end (per BP078 canon `feedback_knight_yoke_wakeup_prompt.md`).
6. **Statute §10 ACCURACY > SPEED** -- better to author the Yoke with precise scope than rush an ambiguous brief that triggers Knight clarification roundtrip.
7. **Truth-Always** -- if the Yoke scope has uncertainty (e.g., schema unknown), surface that uncertainty in the brief rather than papering over.

